article.headline: Towson 75, W. Michigan 73
article.story: TOWSON, Md. -- Isaiah Philmore made a jumpshot with 0.3 seconds remaining to give Towson a 75-73 win over Western Michigan on Wednesday night. Philmore's shot capped a 24-7 run by the Tigers (2-3), who trailed by 15, 66-51, with 10:19 left. Towson took a 72-71 lead with 1:53 to play, as part of the big run. A free throw from Troy Franklin with 28 seconds left extended the Tigers' lead to two, 73-71. Mike Douglas tied it at 73 for Western Michigan on a layup with 14 seconds to play. Philmore hit the game-winning jumper after Towson grabbed an offensive rebound off Franklin's jumper with 2 seconds remaining. Juwan Howard, Jr. and Nate Hutcheson scored 13 each for the Broncos (1-4). Douglas added a career-high 13 assists -- the second highest single-game total in school history. Franklin scored 22 points, Braxton Dupree scored 21 and grabbed 14 rebounds for the Tigers.
